 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the data that identifies a product group, which collects
     products that share a common activity.
   </p>
   <p>
     The product group identifies products that need to be included within
     a group for a specific purpose.  It specifies the group with: 
   </p>

     <ul>
       <!-- 
       <li>Identification of the group members;</li>
       <li>Purpose of grouping these products;</li>
       <li>Product group boundary.</li>
       -->
       <li>
         Identification of a set of products grouped together for a common
         purpose, such as sales/marketing, analysis, production, usage, support
         activity, support solution, disposing;
       </li>

       <li>Identification of a group as a subset of another group;</li> 
       
       <li>Reference to the stakeholder for the group, who causes the creation of the group;</li> 
       
       <li>
         List of common characteristics, which is shared by the members of
         the group, for instance scheduled for maintenance, sales, upgrading;
       </li>

       <li>The reason for grouping these products.</li>
     </ul>
     <p>
       The grouping is irrespective of having a common part type, number, owner,
       assembly.
     </p>
 </purpose>

